    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>F1 Score</strong> becomes 1 only when <strong>precision</strong> and <strong>recall </strong>are both 1. <strong>F1 score </strong>becomes high only when both <strong>precision</strong> and<strong> recall</strong> are high. <strong>F1 score</strong> is the harmonic mean of <strong>precision</strong> and <strong>recall</strong> and is a better measure than <strong>accuracy</strong>.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In the pregnancy example, <strong>F1 Score</strong> = 2* ( 0.857 * 0.75)/(0.857 + 0.75) = 0.799.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
